      "content": "The data from cities that have implemented congestion pricing shows a clear reduction in traffic volume and associated emissions, making it an empirically sound environmental tool. It is not merely \"one way of looking at it\"; it is a proven mechanism for internalizing the external costs of driving in dense urban cores. To meet aggressive climate goals, these market-based interventions are increasingly recognized as necessary complements to regulatory measures.",
      "source": "target",
